            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_es.00328.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office.<ptr
                            target="loc.07231_n1"/><lb/>ASYLUM FOR THE INSANE<lb/>LONDON.<lb/>
                        ONTARIO<lb/>London, Ont.,</name><date when="1888-09-03" rend="right"
                            ><handShift rend="manuscript"/>3 Sept <handShift rend="printed"
                            />188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>8</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>I have your note of 31st written on "November Boughs"<ptr target="n3999"/> paper&#8212;it is first class
                and will make a handsome book&#8212;I hope you will not trim the margins but leave
                the paper its full size&#8212;of course you will not trim the margins in vol. of
                C.W.s<ptr target="n4151"/>? The weather here is wonderful&#8212;so cool, bright and cheery&#8212;the
                place looks well&#8212;autumn flowers at their best&#8212;I fear, dear Walt, you are
                feeling pretty miserable but you must not give up&#8212;there is a glorious future
                ahead of you yet.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">RM Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
